caption: Great lamb dishes! Yum!! Going to try the lamb burrito or chicken mole next. Very friendly staff. I had been cycling past this place for 25+ years and finally stopped in. Old school mid century Cal-Mex food, reminded me of Rose Cafe in Santa Barbara. And gave me a food (& her smile) anchor during the pandemic.
A chimichanga here is 2 small burritos about 3 inches long by and inch wide...a chimichanga in texas is one bit large fried thick burrito
Excellent take out experience! Super duper staff! Almost 40 years open; Chimichangas rock!!!
The best in the island!!!!  36yrs and still going strong!!!!

Hands down the worst all pastor and birria I have ever had in my life. Wait worst Mexican food.  The  burrito was rock hard and dry. They forgot my rice and beans. The "guac" was tomatoes and some inedible green paste. I never write reviews but they need a new chef if they want to stay in business.
Good food, fast service
The lady (assuming owner/chef) was genuinely nice when we first stepped in the door. Answered all the questions we had. Food was above average around this area (from socal). Would eat here again
Enchiladas need to bake much longer.

Ate here one evening and had the chile relleno potatoes and it was so delicious I had to return the next evening for more of the same. Chips and salsa were also delicious. And the staff was just wonderful. Definitely good food and worth a visit.
Tacos aren't  authentic needs two tortillas no lime onnions and celentro.

Not worth the price. I am pregnant and have been craving Mexican food. Their food is not that great. I ordered a chicken quesadilla and chilli rellanos neither we're worth the price. Very disappointed that there was actually good reviews for this place. Rice and beans aren't even good either. They smell burnt.

I usually don't leave bad reviews. That being said the staff was AWESOME much aloha. BUT..... don't believe the pictures my burrito was tiny and sad having almost no flavor and half the meat I had to spit out because it was FULL of gristle $10.50 for a $3 burrito I was SOOOOO disappointed. The burrito in the pic is tiny and still not even full. Sorry guys but if you want to stay in business you better step it up ALOT $10 better be a burrito that fills the whole container or at least more than half.
Chicken burrito so delicious
They are always so kind.... make everything from scratch. Great food and great people!

Ordered enchiladas, chicken soup and chips and salsa through grub hub. Not only the soup didn’t have any broth, it also came in a double bowl. The inner layer bowl’s bottom was missing. It was clearly dropped. The tortillas in the enchiladas were undercooked and not covered in sauce, just cheese. Oh and they didn’t get our order right. Do not order from this place.
Great food and great service
Great service and the lamb quesadilla was amazing
This place is Mexican approved.
Whew, it is soooo good. My belly 🥰 I'll definitely visit again. Mahalo 🤙🏾
great food! The crowbar was a fine choice!
Food so so. Nice owner and has been here for decades so it's popular.

Everything is over priced when you consider all the food is microwaved. The Mole was horrible along with the chile relleno which is what I ordered today. Very disappointed Better of at Mexico's Restaurant.
I'm from Oregon.  There's a mexican restaurant on every corner... really hard to find good Mexican food in hawaii... really delicious...
So.e of the best Mexican food in town  Very authentic shredded beef and not hamburger K so good
Ate there for lunch. They had what I was craving for and it was good
Great Mexican cuisine, good prices & great service.  Mucho bueno!
Not what id call mexican food

The staff were pretty friendly but was a bit confused when ordering, my family and I wanted to eat Mexican food so badly. I basically ordered nearly everything on the menu. Spent close to a hundred dollars. Then I noticed that they were using the microwave to heat up the food or melt the dang cheese and I panicked, that in its self says food will taste awful. I felt bad if I were to cancel. But I thought I will give it a chance. The tamales was awesome loved it . Everything else I would take another bite. And I am a big girl I was starving but just couldn’t take another bite. Hope to give you another chance in the future
Loved it. Best food on the island. And they didn't even know it. It's all done out of the love of good food.
(Translated by Google) Magnificent food that Rachel makes I recommend  (Original) Magnifica comida que hace Raquel se las recomiendo

This little place is amazing. Will absolutely be back. I got the steak ala mexicana and I will say it was pretty spicy but the flavor was amazing. My wife devoured the carne asada and I tried a bit if it. Delicious and tender. The salsa is fresh made salsa and the flavor is just right. Amazing amazing place. I recommend if you are in the area then stood by and get some delicious mexican food.
Gave a two-star review a couple of months ago. Reordered because I really wanted Mexican food, and I'm glad I did. The product is much better this time
Never again
Awesome.  Fresh!

Very authentic! It's not your typical Mexican restaurant. If you ever had Mexica food in Mexico then you gonna love this place. It's all about the beans. It would be difficult to order because the menu has all kinds of choices.
I remember coming here in the early 80s. This place is still going - that is something else! Always loved the food here, it is always prepared just right!
Nice employees, food was pretty good, could be better spiced, although that might be a personal preference. A little expensive for a hole in the wall.
Softest most delicious lamb burrito. Best homemade Mexican food in town.
Love the food
Excellent service, delicious food! The Molé is great
Far better service than most restaurants! A small "hole in the wall" with authentic Mexican food. Definitely worth checking out.
Amazing food. Real family owned environment, super nice employees and did I mention amazing food?!
(Translated by Google) ONO-licious  (Original) ONO-LICIOUS
Awesome authentic Mexican food. Been eating here for over 30 years. Prices are very reasonable .
Neat little shop, bring your own beer, friendly service and good food. First time I ever had lamb tacos 😊

Love this "hole in the wall" spot!! Food is great, service is AWESOME! They do use the cater services like Uber eats but swing by sometimes and eat in. Talk stories with aunty Rochelle and them. No forget BYOB 🍻🙃
Fast friendly service. Great food.
food was amazing! the noodle soup is my favorite and the drinks are amazingg! The food took a little while but usually is very fast, the staff was super nice too, great little family spot
Very good and authentic Mexican food.
Authentic! I enjoyed every bite!

I have always loved Mexican food, and I've had it everywhere from Mexico to Canada and in between; but this place is like nowhere I've been before. The small and simple dining area is unnoticed once you receive your chips and homemade salsa. Amazing food, go see for yourself...

Great authentic Mexican food! A little place, but great service and salsa was delicious!!! I had chicken soup and was very tasty. Owner was very sweet and attentive. Might be best, authentic Mexican food in Honolulu. Highly recommend.
Loved the carnitas burrito!!
Just as good as I remembered it being back in 2007 when I ate it for the first time... Food still incredible and the ladies are just as sweet as ever.

I don't know how this place has four stars... My wife and I ordered a vegetable chimichanga and a beef chimichanga each plate consisting of two pieces. Somehow we each got one veg chimichanga and one beef chimichanga on each plate. An odd mix up of the order. The beans were not good and the salsa that came with the chips we're also not good. There are definitely better Mexican restaurants on the island than this.
Friendly staff, fast service ,tasty food, fantastic prices.
Cool hole in the wall. Good food, great service
Chicken chimichunga is the best ever. Plus it's BYOB with no corkage fee!!!
Simply the best Mexican restaurant in Honolulu  delicious homemade Mexican food
Rochelle is the bomb!!!
Everything we ordered was good accepting the tortilla chips. We ordered take out and discovered the chips were rancid. Nasty experience.
Always nice going there, they make you feel so welcome and the food is fantastic!
We had a great meal...great service... friendly and reasonably priced..... excellent
Really nice person running place. Just her And she makes great food😉
Small restaurant with delicious lunch plates.
a must if your in the town area
Lamb chimichanga. The bomb.
Always feels like family

My husband and I ate at El Burrito at least once a week when we were stationed at Hickam Air Force Base in 1988 - 1990. We couldn't get enough of the salsa! We finally made it back to visit in 2017... And we'were delighted to find that the little restaurant hasn't changed. Still delicious food and the friendliest service. The girl who was our young waitress in the 80's is now the owner. It was a delight to see her again.
Home style awesome food nuff said
I was not impressed by their food.
Had the 2 potato chimichanga with rice and beans. Everything was tasty! Very friendly staff.

El Burrito is by far the best Mexican restaurant in Hawaii.  They are family run and our children grew up going here every week.  They are friendly, the food is authentic and the vegetarian choices are wonderful.  They make the very best vegetarian chimichanga ever!!
i was there years and I know that it is goood.

I ate here years ago,  so for the icky reviews.. ..shame on them. This place is authentic mexican food, and so.... gooood! I'll post again when I'm done today...I'm treating me to a birthday lunch!  Ok & Ole'.  Had lunch there.  Excellent!  The only thing I'd change is ..go back to free chips with salsa, like everyone else
To Damian raise I think this is a very good restaurant and I think taco bell sucks go eat up your nasty taco bell
Very tasty rice, burrito excellent, chips  & salsa ohhh so good!

Have been going there for 30 years and one of the only authentic mexican restaurants on the island.  Always have good experience there.  Good food.  Beats taco bell or UGH that gross so called mexican food restaurant in Haleiwa Cholo's. Bad reviews from Gringos...what can you expect.
Not worth it... save the extra couple dollars and just go to taco bell.
